    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-07T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-07T10:00:00-05:00" n="289"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d289">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">871.01/12–744: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The American Representative in Rumania</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Berry</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-07T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 7, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 8—6:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>49. The new Rumanian Government has formally been announced today and is
                    constituted with General Radescu<note n="80" xml:id="d289fn1">Gen. Nicolae
                        Radescu, formerly Rumanian Chief of Staff.</note> as both Prime Minister and
                    Minister of the Interior. General Negulescu<note n="81" xml:id="d289fn2">Gen.
                        Ion Negulescu.</note> is War Minister and General Stanescu<note n="82"
                        xml:id="d289fn3">Brig. Gen. Virgil Stanescu.</note> is Under Secretary of
                    Interior for National Security. Portfolio of General Damaceanu<note n="83"
                        xml:id="d289fn4">Brig. Gen. I. Dimitru Damaceanu, a signer of the Rumanian
                        armistice.</note> for liaison with the Allies and application of the
                    armistice has been dropped. To give National Peasant Party vote lost by
                    relinquishing Interior Ministry post, it is planned to add an additional
                    ministry without portfolio. Otherwise the cabinet of the second Sanatescu
                    government remains intact.</p>
                <p>A government program was announced to which all participants subscribed at the
                    first cabinet meeting. It includes reestablishing order, maintaining production
                    and factory discipline, observance of the armistice agreement, disarming members
                    of all party organizations (the Communists alone had not disarmed), weeding out
                    state administrative personnel of Fascist elements, abrogating all racial laws
                    and prosecution of war criminals.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berry</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
